İstanbul, Türkiye","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Doukas","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Greek Spyros, Anastasios, Aphrodite, Apostolos, Athanasios, Constantine, Costas, Dimitrios, Kalliopi, Kimon, Panagiotis.","Greek: from medieval Greek <i>doukas</i> ‘duke, lord’, from Latin <i>dux</i>. This was the name of a family of imperial rank in medieval Byzantium."],"variants":[{"name":"Dukas","meanings":["Greek: variant of   Doukas  ."]}]},{"name":"George","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Via Old French and Latin, from Greek <i>Georgios</i> (a derivative of <i>geōrgos</i> ‘farmer’, from <i>gē</i> ‘earth’ + <i>ergein</i> ‘to work’). This was the name of several early saints, including the shadowy figure who is now the patron of England (as well as of Germany and Portugal). If the saint existed at all, he was perhaps martyred in Palestine in the persecutions of Christians instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  at the beginning of the 4th century. The popular legend in which the hero slays a dragon is a medieval Italian invention. He was for a long time a more important saint in the Orthodox Church than in the West, and the name was not much used in England during the Middle Ages, even after  St George  came to be regarded as the patron of England in the 14th century. Its use increased from the 1400s, and by  1500  it was regularly among the most popular male names. This popularity was reinforced when  George I  came to the throne in  1714 , bringing this name with him from Germany. It has been one of the most popular English boys' names ever since."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"George Palaiologos Doukas Komnenos was born about 1125 as the son of Despota Alessio Paleologo and Anna Komnene Doukaina. He had at least 2 sons. He registered for military service in 1199. In 1167, at the age of 43, his occupation is listed as led a diplomatic mission to the kingdom of jerusalem, escorting manuel i's niece maria komnene to marry king amalric of jerusalem.. He died about 1167, in İstanbul, Türkiye, at the age of 44."},"et":{"ABT 1125–ABT 1167":"umbes 1125–umbes 1167","1125–1167":"1125–1167","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1145–1203":"1145–1203","1150–1247":"1150–1247","1087–1125":"1087–1125","1247":"1247","1203":"1203","1125":"1125","1167":"1167","ABT 1167":"umbes 1167","1145":"1145","ABT 1125":"umbes 1125","1087":"1087","1162":"1162","1150":"1150","after 1125":"pärast 1125","Istanbul, Türkiye":"İstanbul, Türgi"},"fi":{"ABT 1125–ABT 1167":"noin 1125–noin 1167","1125–1167":"1125–1167","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1145–1203":"1145–1203","1150–1247":"1150–1247","1087–1125":"1087–1125","1247":"1247","1203":"1203","1125":"1125","1167":"1167","ABT 1167":"noin 1167","1145":"1145","ABT 1125":"noin 1125","1087":"1087","1162":"1162","1150":"1150","after 1125":"1125 jälkeen","Istanbul, Türkiye":"İstanbul, Turkki"},"fr":{"ABT 1125–ABT 1167":"environ 1125–environ 1167","1125–1167":"1125–1167","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1145–1203":"1145–1203","1150–1247":"1150–1247","1087–1125":"1087–1125","1247":"1247","1203":"1203","1125":"1125","1167":"1167","ABT 1167":"environ 1167","1145":"1145","ABT 1125":"environ 1125","1087":"1087","1162":"1162","1150":"1150","after 1125":"après 1125","Istanbul, Türkiye":"İstanbul, Turquie","lifeSummary":"George Palaiologos Doukas Komnenos est né environ 1125, fils de Despota Alessio Paleologo et Anna Komnene Doukaina. Il a eu au moins 2 fils. Il s'est inscrite au service militaire en 1199. En 1167, à l’âge de 43 ans, sa profession de son indiquée est led a diplomatic mission to the kingdom of jerusalem, escorting manuel i's niece maria komnene to marry king amalric of jerusalem.. Il est décédé environ 1167, à İstanbul, Turquie, à l’âge de 44 ans."},"de":{"ABT 1125–ABT 1167":"um 1125–um 1167","1125–1167":"1125–1167","